Task 7: REST API Contract - Today Window Query Evidence
=====================================================

Evidence for: Query today window for one mac/interface

Test Environment: Linux container (mock mode)
Build Status: PASS
Test Status: PASS

API Implementation:
------------------
GET /api/v1/traffic?window=today

Supported windows: all, 30days, 7days, today, month

Query Parameters:
- window: Required. Valid values: all, 30days, 7days, today, month
- interface: Optional. Filter by interface name
- mac: Optional. Filter by MAC address (XX:XX:XX:XX:XX:XX format)
- limit: Optional. Max records to return (default 100, max 1000)
- offset: Optional. Records to skip for pagination (default 0)

Response Format:
---------------
{
  "window": "today",
  "limit": 100,
  "offset": 0,
  "records": [
    {
      "interface": "eth0",
      "ifindex": 2,
      "mac": "aa:bb:cc:dd:ee:ff",
      "ingress_bytes": 12345,
      "egress_bytes": 6789,
      "total_bytes": 19134,
      "ingress_packets": 100,
      "egress_packets": 50,
      "total_packets": 150,
      "window": "today"
    }
  ]
}

Error Responses:
---------------
HTTP 400 - Invalid window or malformed MAC:
{
  "error": "invalid window, must be one of: all, 30days, 7days, today, month"
}
or
{
  "error": "invalid mac format, must be XX:XX:XX:XX:XX:XX"
}

HTTP 500 - Server error:
{
  "error": "error message"
}

MAC Validation:
--------------
MAC must match regex: ^([0-9A-Fa-f]{2}:){5}[0-9A-Fa-f]{2}$

